Author::::Hangerhead
DateTime::::2016-03-05T17:34:29Z
for the no-knead bread, I think it's meant to be better if the pot (dutch-oven) has also been heated in the oven to begin with. Then drop the dough into it, lid on and then back into the ovem. This allows a very rapid introduction of a sealed amount of steam (the dough is quite high in moisture), and so the crust becomes very crisp (sourdough).I've also made my own sourdough starter and use this now as the base for all subsequent no-knead breads.



