Author::::sunshinefairy
DateTime::::2016-03-05T14:08:03Z
We don't get buttermilk here, so I use half yogurt/half ordinary milk for anything that requires buttermilk. Also, I make my own ricotta (also don't get that here and the nearest Turkish equivalent is way too salty for cheesecake), and I use the leftover whey from this instead of buttermilk. It is very acidic, so does exactly the same job - perfect for soda bread and makes wonderfully light scones as well (use instead of the milk in the recipe). It keeps in the fridge for a few days after you've done the separation - it does look a bit unlikely, as it is clear, but don't let that put you off.



Author::::todobien
